commentary: MM Sharma to Masakadza, OUT Jadeja's taken aim and demolished the stumps at the bowler's end and Masakadza is short of the crease! Masakadza pushed a slower ball towards point and set off. Jadeja got to the ball quickly from point, picked up with his left hand and flung the ball at the stumps in one smooth motion. That's his second direct hit run-out in two games.

commentary: Waller to Raina, no run fullish and outside off, Raina tries to steer it to on side again but the turn beats him and is he stumped here? He came out while trying to drive and Taylor unsettled the bails in no time. The third umpire has been called for, it's a very close call. And it seems like Raina might have made it back, replays are not so conclusive and it's given not out
